Review: Solid ramen for affordable price. Surprisingly veggie dishes are well made and broth is very spicy. Tasted great.
Solid ambiance in the marina. Beautiful area. Service is amazing. Portion sizes are massive. Overall great brunch spot.
It was great! Didn't eat the sushi because I was craving Ramen. I know this place is known for its sushi, but don't sleep on the Ramen.
I'd go here JUST for their garlic knots. It's delectable af
Amazing food, massive portions. Huge fan of the tea leaf salad.
Great late night food, solid portion sizes, hits the spot when you’re in the mood for something to warm you up.
Really good vibes, great for large group settings (outdoor available). Food comes fast and is vegetarian friendly. Overall solid Mexican food.
Enchiladas were so good. A little too cheesy, but it hit the spot. Danky af
The food was good for the amount we paid. A little disappointed that the chole was bland and lacked spice.
Some of the healthiest food you can find in the city. There’s something there everyone. It’s always packed, especially in the evenings, so try to make a reservation.
Solid ambiance, cute vibes, phenomenal drinks, worth the value
If you’re in the mood for the worst best food, this is the place to be. Food is incomplete without seniores saucy so make sure you get that.
I don't care how many times I have bougie, arthouse pizza, domino's will always hit the spot, especially the pan pizza
Out of all the deep dishes I’ve tried in the bay, this place is the best. Quality is amazing, you won’t be hungry after eating this.
The brunch buffet is always a vibe. I know $39 may seem steep but with bottomless margs and unlimited juice it's a fantastic deal for large groups to chill
